# Agent toolchain roadmap

Status: **Phases 2–5 scaffold shipped** — tools sidecar, HAR/Blitz API, speech edit lane.

Home: [[index]] · CLI plan: [[docs/CLI]]

## Goal

Ship a **verb-indexed agent surface** so any model (Cursor, Claude Code, Codex, Pi) can:

1. Install Reactable (app + CLI + skills)
2. Author decks and record on the native stage
3. Post with ffmpeg and/or HyperFrames
4. Call bundled native tools (ffmpeg, ASR, VAD, isolation, HAR) from the CLI

Progressive disclosure: thin `SKILL.md` → `verbs/*.md` → upstream skills (hyperframes, gsap).

---

## Phase 1 — Skills + install (now)

| Item | Status | Path |
|------|--------|------|
| Skill manifest (source of truth) | done | `skill/manifest.json` |
| CI compile → registry + skills.sh JSON | done | `scripts/compile-skills.ts` |
| Verb-indexed references | done | `skill/verbs/*.md` |
| `reactable skills prompt` | done | `cli/lib/agent-prompt.ts` |
| `reactable install app` | done | `cli/lib/app-install.ts` |
| Bar → Copy agent prompt | done | `BarPanel` gear menu |
| skills.sh publish manifest | done | `skill/dist/skills.sh.json` |
| Publish to skills.sh (manual) | pending | register repo on skills.sh |

```bash
bun run scripts/compile-skills.ts
reactable skills install --user
reactable skills prompt --deck showcase
```

